article.description: Sherwyn Devonish-Prince Jr. made all three of his 3-point shot attempts, the last one with four seconds left, and Morgan State beat Coppin State 50-48 on Saturday.
article.headline: Morgan St. clips Coppin St. in 50-48 win
article.linkText: Morgan St. clips Coppin St. in 50-48 win
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Sherwyn Devonish-Prince Jr. made all three of his 3-point shot attempts, the last one with four seconds left, and Morgan State beat Coppin State 50-48 on Saturday. Dejuan Clayton made two free throws with 23 seconds left to give the Eagles a 48-47 lead before Morgan State called timeout setting up Devonish-Prince's game winner. Stanley Davis led the Bears (10-12, 4-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) with 13 points and 10 rebounds while Devonish-Prince scored 11 points. David Syfax Jr. grabbed nine rebounds. Andrew Robinson led Coppin State with 12 points while Brendan Medley-Bacon pulled down a career-high 24 rebounds -- seven on the offensive end. His rebound effort matched single-game high totals set this season by George Washington's Arnaldo Toro Barea and Hasahn French of Saint Louis entering Saturday's games. Medley-Bacon was named the MEAC's Co-Player of the Week on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
